        "impacts": "The entire Broads Area is extremely low lying, with much of it at or below sea level. The Broadland Futures Initiative Study Area, which covers the Broads and its hinterland, estimates that 75% of it is influenced by potential flooding. \\nhttps://www.broads-authority.gov.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0026/374345/The-Influence-Of-Flood-Risk-Management-Within-The-Plan-Area-Web-based-version.pdf\\n\\nThe primary increase in risk will come from increased sea level rise - the dates when this will become critical and the extent of the increase of risk still has a wide margin of uncertainty.",
