        "focusAreas": "Resilience|Energy|Finance|Emissions reduction|Adaptation",
        "description": "Cambridgeshire County Council chairs the ADEPT Energy & Clean Growth Working Group which is made up of 40+ representatives from local authorities across the UK. The group is used to share best practice and knowledge, and to bring together key messages to be shared with national government via a DESNZ rep who sits on the group. Other organisations (e.g. charities, businesses, community groups etc.) are also invited to attend adhoc meetings to share their work with the group.",
