        "refId": "Mitigation Action 7",
        "sector": "Other sectoral action: Finance and Economic Development > Instruments to fund low carbon projects",
        "description": "Infuse builds innovation expertise in Wales' public, voluntary and private sectors and supports new models of service delivery across the Cardiff Capital Region. To address the pressing climate crisis, the aim of the Infuse Collision Space was to give people and organisations the skills, tools and the space they need to collaborate and create ambitious change to accelerate the journey to net zero. The challenge for the Infuse Collision Space was developed in collaboration with system leaders and key stakeholders across the Cardiff Capital Region and was used to provide a focus for the innovation and experiments of participants. Challenge: to support a just transition to net zero within public sector transportation across the Cardiff Capital Region.\\ninfuse-summary-report-english-120525.pdf",
        "status": "2024",
        "cobenefits": "2025",
        "financeStatus": "None of the above impacts associated with this action have been measured",
