        "vulnerableGroups": "Outdoor workers|Indigenous peoples|Low-income households|Women and girls|Children and youth|Marginalized/minority communities|Elderly|Vulnerable health groups",
        "sectorsExposed": "Manufacturing|Human health and social work activities|Sewerage, waste management and remediation activities|Financial and insurance activities|Conservation|Mining and quarrying|Education|Arts, entertainment and recreation|Water supply|Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply|Transportation and storage|Waste management|Construction|Agriculture|Forestry|Fishing|Accommodation and food service activities",
        "impacts": "Extreme cold days (within the general winter temperature ranges) is a risk multiplier for excess winter deaths and winter hardship for some of our poorest and most vulnerable population. There is a clear link to the quality and standards of homes and accommodation across the district as referenced in the Retrofit evidence provided in this submission. The is an extensive range of hard-to-treat and historical property,especially in some of the poorest neighbourhoods so the issue is a factor of hazard, exposure and vulnerability. Our work on homelessness and rough-sleeping and the strategy (2020 approved version) is also of relevance - and again the implications of Covid-19 and more immediate responses to rough-sleepers will be monitored and addressed over the next and forthcoming winters.\\nThe impact of cold on vulnerable groups is considered withing our JOINT STRATEGIC NEEDS ASSESSMENT on housing and health - \\nhttps://jsna.bradford.gov.uk/media/mbpkpb13/housing-and-health-april-2025.pdf",
