        "sector": "Stationary energy: Domestic and/or commercial heat network",
        "description": "Development of Bradford Energy Network (BEN)\\n\\nBradford Council is working with partners to develop the Bradford Energy Network (BEN) which is a \u00a370million low emission centralised heat system, based in the city centre and distributing energy via pipes, utilising one of the UK's largest air-source heat pump networks. The Council is on track to connect City Hall to the network. City Hall's connection sees the countries first Grade 1 listed building to join a heat network and that more city centre buildings - including St George's Hall and the Alhambra are likely to join in the near future. The University of Bradford, Bradford College and the Law Courts are also joining as part of their own net-zero commitments.\\n\\nhttps://www.thetelegraphandargus.co.uk/news/25187592.city-hall-linked-new-low-carbon-heat-network/\\n\\nhttps://1energy.uk/networks/bradford-energy-network/\\n\\nBradford Council is also working with North East and Yorkshire Net Zero Hub to support the proliferation of heat networks via heat network zoning.\\n\\nPlease note the above Mitigation Actions in this section are just a small selection of a much wider range of actions which are summarised in our Climate Action Plan.",
