        "sector": "Transportation: Development of low emission zones",
        "description": "Clean Air Zone (CAZ)\\n\\nContinue to improve the District's Air Quality through the ongoing delivery of the CAZ and regular air quality monitoring \\n\\nThe positive health impacts of CAZ were recently underlined in a report produced by Born in Bradford.\\n\\n'The study compared a two-year period between 2018 and 2020, before the plan was introduced, with a similar timescale between 2021 and 2023.\\nIt then analysed the number of patients seeking help from their GP or emergency departments for respiratory or cardiovascular problems.\\nThe study found there were 598 fewer GP visits by patients with respiratory health problems per month, and 134 fewer monthly visits by patients with cardiovascular issues.\\nInitial findings estimated the reduced burden on GP appointments could be saving the NHS more than \u00a330,000 each month.'\\n\\nAbove quote taken from the following BBC article:\\n\\nhttps://www.bbc.co.uk/news/articles/clyvnq1lnrpo\\n\\nFurther details can be found below:\\n\\nhttps://www.bradford.gov.uk/clean-air-zone/clean-air-zone/\\n\\nClean Air Zone net proceeds are invested in to carbon emissions reduction and zero emission transport projects. \\n\\nThe CAZ is also expected to reduce emissions of CO2e by 147,000 tones during its lifetime. \\n\\nPlease note the above Mitigation Actions in this section are just a small selection of a much wider range of actions which are summarised in our Climate Action Plan.",
