        "impacts": "Leicester has a number of areas at risk from river flooding, and has previously experienced disruptive flooding events. Climate change is expected to increase the likelihood and scale of flooding locally. Large scale adaptation work has already been carried out by the council's Flood Risk team to remove properties from flood risk, and lower the risk. The greatest risks are to life and property in flood risk areas, particularly for the most vulnerable groups. It is known that certain communities are more vulnerable to this hazard due to the areas and homes they live in. Flood risk mapping has identified the communities and properties most at risk, and this includes some less well-off communities. There are a number of businesses in flood risk areas that could face significant disruption and costs in the event of flooding. One of the city's major NHS sites is also in an at-risk area, meaning that the health-impacts of flooding could be compounded by wider disruption of health services. A number of schools are also in at-risk areas, which could disrupt education provision in the city.",
