        "comment": "Manchester engages across multiple government levels to integrate climate action with health inequality reduction through four key partnerships:\\nRegional Partnership: Greater Manchester Health and Care Partnership (GMHCP) devolution enables localised climate-health decision-making and coordination across health sectors, supporting climate-resilient health systems implementation. https://gmintegratedcare.org.uk/greatermanchester-icp/ \\nNational Collaboration: Partnership with NHS England on the NHS Adaptation Plan delivers strategies for climate-resilient healthcare facilities, including infrastructure upgrades and climate integration into health service planning. https://www.england.nhs.uk/greenernhs/a-net-zero-nhs/adaptation/ \\n Local Health Trust: Direct collaboration with Manchester Foundation Trust on the Green Plan reduces NHS carbon footprint and promotes healthcare sustainability, aligning with regional climate goals. https://mft.nhs.uk/app/uploads/2022/02/MFT-Green-Plan_V1.0.pdf \\nStrategic Integration: Making Manchester Fairer plan addresses health inequalities while ensuring climate actions improve health outcomes for all residents, focusing on reducing preventable health disparities. https://www.manchester.gov.uk/download/downloads/id/28867/making_manchester_fairer_plan_pdf.pdf \\n"
