        "focusAreas": "Waste|Natural environment|Adaptation|Resilience|Water|Transport (Mobility)|Energy",
        "description": "The Greater Manchester Strategic Infrastructure Board (GMSIB) https://www.greatermanchester-ca.gov.uk/what-we-do/planning-and-housing/strategic-infrastructure/ plays a crucial role in aligning infrastructure development with regional goals outlined in the GM Infrastructure Strategy 2040. It represents a significant example of collaboration across government, business, and civil society.\\n\\nKey Aspects of Collaboration:\\n\\nGovernment:\\n\\nAlignment with Policy: GMSIB coordinates with national and local government agencies to ensure that regional infrastructure projects align with broader policy objectives, including climate resilience and net-zero targets.\\nIntegrated Planning: The Board facilitates integrated planning and investment decisions that address both local and national priorities, promoting cohesive and efficient infrastructure development.\\nBusiness:\\n\\nPrivate Sector Engagement: GMSIB works closely with businesses to leverage private sector expertise and investment in infrastructure projects. This collaboration helps to identify innovative solutions and secure funding for major initiatives.\\nInfrastructure Investment: By aligning business interests with regional needs, the Board supports the development of critical infrastructure that drives economic growth and enhances regional connectivity.",
