        "focusAreas": "Resilience|Emissions reduction|Inclusive climate action and/or equity|Adaptation",
        "description": "MAST - Manchester Arts Sustainability Team was established in 2011 as a network of arts and cultural organisations who came together to understand how they could contribute to the delivery of our city's first Climate Change Strategy.In 2021 they became GMAST. GMAST aims to reduce the environmental impact of the cultural and creative community by working collectively to tackle the climate and ecological crisis. Working together they share knowledge and build capacity for practical action. Collectively they drive change in our sector and beyond for the benefit of our communities. GMAST brings together over 60 cultural organisations across Greater Manchester. They are aligned to the Paris Agreement to limit global warming and endorse the target of becoming net-zero no later than 2038. They play our full part in Manchester's Zero Carbon Framework. Our collaborative model works, is internationally recognised and they want share it.",
        "otherEntities": "NGO and associations|Residents/community groups|Communication Services|Climate initiatives/networks"
