        "sector": "Agriculture, Forestry and Land Use: Green space and/ or biodiversity preservation and expansion",
        "description": "Biodiversity Net Gain https://www.cornwall.gov.uk/planning-and-building-control/planning-policy/adopted-plans/cornwall-planning-for-biodiversity-guide/\\n10% Biodiversity Net Gain within planning requirements for major buildings. This is included within the formally adopted Climate Emergency Development Planning Document published in February 2023. The Cornwall Climate Emergency Development Plan Document includes minor developments in its biodiversity net gain policy. However, this has now been superseded by a nationally mandated requirement for developments on small sites to apply BNG. Cornwall Council has publicised this change through its website and the Planning Agents forum.",
