        "focusAreas": "Energy",
        "description": "Local Area Energy Planning (LAEP) - Awarded \u00a3500,000 from BEIS to deliver a Local Area Energy Plan to provide Cornwall and the Isles of Scilly with a practical roadmap as to how a net zero energy system can be achieved. Project commenced April 2023 and was completed in March 2025. The LAEP utilises a new, place-based approach that enables areas to develop their plans to decarbonise local energy systems. The Plan addresses the complex interactions of power, gas, heat, and transport, and the many ways in which future energy may be supplied, managed, and consumed within Cornwall and the Isles of Scilly. The Local Area Energy Plan is necessary to inform strategic planning, investments and decision-making, leading to the first net zero region that captures the 'benefits of decarbonising our local energy system to promote a prosperous and resilient economy and a just transition to a more sustainable future.' The plan for a resilient economy and a fair and inclusive society, will support the ambition for floating offshore wind and deep geothermal, inform future programmes to retrofit our homes and commercial and public buildings, investment in our energy and transport infrastructure, as well as identifying potential sites for renewables and energy storage to support sustainable growth and development for Cornwall and the Isles of Scilly. As a place-based plan for a low-carbon transition, the Plan will help facilitate the creation of an integrated position between planning and energy - enabling transport, housing and economic planning decisions relating to energy (supply and demand) to be viewed holistically and enable delivery against an agreed holistic strategy. Collaboration on the development of the plan has included working with key business stakeholders and also the establishment of a Residents' Energy Panel. Phase 1 (development of the LAEP) is now complete and Phase 2 (delivery) is underway.",
        "otherEntities": "Residents/community groups|Construction|Academia|Agriculture|Neighboring local government|Energy|Utilities"
