        "description": "The Environmental Growth Strategy provides a framework for Cornwall & The Isles of Scilly to conserve and grow nature. The refreshed Environmental Growth Strategy (2020-2065) set an enhanced long-term commitment to restore the natural environment to not just conserve, but to grow nature and respond to the Ecological Emergency. The strategy is structured around 10 'pillars' for nature along with four enabling ambitions and two milestones including the target that 30% of our land, rivers and seas will be positively managed for nature by 2030. The Strategy acknowledges that good environmental growth is about enhancing nature - ensuring that there is more of it, and that it is bigger, better, more diverse and more joined up.",
