        "description": "UK100 Countryside Climate Network (CCN) Kate Kennally, CEO Cornwall Council is a member of the UK100 Countryside Climate Network (CCN). The CCN amplifies the voice of rural communities as part of our national policy advocacy. Rural communities are at the front of climate impacts but are also at the forefront of climate action. As a member of the CCN, made up of ambitious local leaders, we are committed to delivering climate action within our local communities and amplifying our rural voice as part of national policy advocacy. The primary purpose is to support a local led rapid transition to Net Zero and Clean Air. This is promoted through collaboration of leaders across the country to learn together, agree priorities on legislative and regulatory change and empower decision makers. Sharing of knowledge, expertise, tools and connections to enable action.\\n\\nIn 2025 Cornwall Council supported the UK100 Local Climate Engagement Resource Hub Project as a steering group member. The Resource Hub provides a toolkit of engagement resources - to promote 'good' climate engagement within local communities. \\n",
