        "impacts": "Coventry and Warwickshire was included in the Met Office's first ever Amber Extreme Heat Warning in June 2021. Prolonged periods of extreme heat during 2018 and 2025 put increased pressure on NHS services with a rise in the number of people with illnesses associated with hot weather, particularly dehydration which can lead to urinary tract infections (UTIs). We expect heatwaves to occur more frequently which will have impacts on both public health as well as infrastructure and services. Extreme Heat is identified as a High Priority Issue by the Adaptation & Resilience Pathway Group of the Climate Change Board.",
