        "sectorsExposed": "Construction|Real estate activities|Waste management|Human health and social work activities|Sewerage, waste management and remediation activities",
        "impacts": "Coventry has a low risk of river flooding, it has two rivers flowing through its boundaries, the River Sherbourne and River Sowe being in the early stages of the river catchment , which have not historically been subject to significant levels of flooding unlike towns and cities further downstream yet the risk is that due to their location there is short notice for reacting to the risk of flooding. \\n The level of flood risk has also significantly increased particularly relating to Pluvial Flooding i.e. surface water run off from heavy rainfall greater than the drainage systems can cope with with increased risk to households and also businesses .",
