        "vulnerableGroups": "Children and youth|Low-income households|Marginalized/minority communities|Elderly|Women and girls",
        "sectorsExposed": "Human health and social work activities|Conservation|Water supply",
        "impacts": "During the heatwave of 2018, Coventry had massive water shortages and although we managed without imposing a hosepipe ban, as temperatures increase, water shortages will be more severe and residents/businesses will be impacted with wider knock-on effects to the economy. Coventry residents were also asked to be 'water-wise' during the 2022 heatwave where temperatures exceeded 40 degrees similar events occurred in 2024 and 2025 and Severn Trent Water working with the Environment Agency managed. A recent study of the July & August 2022 heatwave incidents cost the West Midlands over \u00a36.3m e.g. costs of fatalities, loss of rail freight journeys etc. The supply is being met with the need for extraction by agriculture and businesses but storage has dropped from 96% in 2022 to 40% https://www.wmca.org.uk/media/zw5dfb2k/economic-impacts-assessment-executive-summary.pdf",
