        "sectorsExposed": "Sewerage, waste management and remediation activities|Water supply|Agriculture|Human health and social work activities|Conservation|Fishing",
        "impacts": "In the last few years due to the reduction in water supply the Environment Agency will not grant businesses and farmers with any new abstraction licenses for the use of significant quantities of water for manufacturing processes in order to be able to keep water levels in water courses sufficiently high enough to sustain freshwater ecosystems. Water is being actively diverted from various water sources in an effort to sustain a sufficient supply for existing businesses and the population. Projections in population growth in coming years will increase the likely demand for water whilst Severn Trent are increasing capacity for water treatment and making significant investments in reducing leaks from the water distribution network. Operation Mighty Oak also recently identified the need to ensure sufficient energy supply as all of the City's water supply is electrically pumped around the City. despite these stresses every person has access to a supply of fresh water that meets the quality standards. It is the freshwater ecosystems that are most impacted upon.",
