        "refId": "Mitigation Action 9",
        "sector": "Transportation: Improve walking, cycling and integrated transit access",
        "description": "New cycleways are being introduced around the city, targeting areas with the poorest air quality as part of the developing Transport Strategy. The first of these have been constructed in Coundon and is a fully segregated route with cycle priorities at junctions. Initiatives encourage cycling around the city, rather than using cars or public transport with the aim to reduce GHG emissions and improve the health and well being of the population. West Midlands Cycle Hire is proving very successful in the city, with 44 docking stations around the city and 300 bikes available. These were being promoted through special offers made for commuters and leisure riders including free rides during the Commonwealth Games and free use of the bikes to residents in the most deprived wards of the city.",
