        "sectors": "Evaluation: Evaluation of plan takes place annually or more frequently than annually|Monitoring: Information on progress of plan is monitored and publicly reported every 3-5 years|Update: Updates to the plan are published annually or more frequently than annually",
        "renewableTarget": "Targets are advised by a Zero Carbon Routemap (attached) for Coventry developed by Professor Gouldson, an economist and environmentalist who has worked closely with Central Government and is founder director of the Economic & Social Research Council's (ESRC) Centre for Climate Change Economics & Policy. His methodology is recognised by the UK Government and has been used to create Zero Carbon Routemaps for other major cities like Edinburgh, Glasgow, Belfast, Leeds, Swansea and Cambridge. The Routemap should inform our target commitments and help the partnership to develop an achievable pathway to net zero in keeping with national and international recommendations. The figures quoted are based upon those identified in the Zero Carbon Routemap an educated estimate conducted by Professor Andy Goulson sustainability advisor to the UK's Investment Bank the figures are a total with an annual investment over the next 15 years of \u00a3145m/yr. Obviously this is not an amaount the City has available as a lump sum but an indicator of the level of investment required across the City to make a zero carbon future possible by the 2050 target date. This applies to and all the other examples listed below they are not funded fully and that a key challenge for the City is to secure funding from whatever sources over time.",
