        "scope": "Same (jurisdiction-wide) - covers entire jurisdiction and nothing else",
        "sectors": "Other: Provides an assessment and overview of priority actions and resulting carbon reductions for the City as a whole",
        "renewableTarget": "Professor Andy Gouldson (senior sustainability advisor to the UK Investment Bank) and his team at Leeds University undertook this study using the same methodology which was used for Glasgow ahead of COP26. I maps out different scenarios and assesses impacts of policy areas on carbon reduction including profiling against targets and prioritising areas of activity to help inform the City's Strategy. The Routemap is a high level strategic document that profiles the priority areas for action and estimated costs at a global level the figures involved are alarming to any organisation working with budgetary limitations this also looks at investment payback and returns from an economic as well as a carbon perspective and was a significant factor in making the case to develop a strategic energy partnership with private investors etc. the figures needed to achieve a zero. The total bill for achieving net zero comes in at \u00a32,175m over a 15 yr period around \u00a3145m/yr.",
