        "mechanisms": "Technical assistance|City business partnership platform|Engineering and consulting procurement|Capacity development|Procurement|Cleaner production industry support|Reporting of climate and/or environmental data|Economic development|Financing (investment)|Circular economy business model support|Project delivery - Public Private Partnership|Climate action plan implementation|Funding (grants)|Requirement to develop and implement emissions reduction target|Labour market training initiatives|Collaborative initiative|Project delivery - Build Operate Transfer|Project implementation and management|Entrepreneurship support programmes|Knowledge or data sharing|Multi-jurisdictional regional collaboratives",
        "focusAreas": null,
        "description": "Eon as the Strategic Energy Partner(SEP) A key milestone in 2024 was the creation of a SEP-led Coventry Energy Plan for the City that developed a vision of the \\nfuture Coventry and clear direction of travel for the SEP's activities and project pipeline. This forms the basis of the delivery \\ndetail for this ABP 2025-26 and provides the strategic direction for the SEP 2025-26 Strategic Goals.\\nAs part of the SEP's commitment, it has developed a Community Benefit Fund (CBF) which will help with delivering outcomes \\nthat benefit the environment and community. In response to growing demand for professionals in Coventry's renewable energy \\nsector, it is committed to recruiting and training apprentices as well as offering work placements while upholding Equality,\\nDiversity and Inclusion (ED&I) principles.\\n4\\nIn 2025/6 the key outputs the SEP intends to deliver are:\\n\u2022 Development and execution of the delivery programmes resulting from the Coventry Energy Plan.\\n\u2022 Assessment, development and implementation of a public sector building decarbonisation programme, starting with schools.\\n\u2022 Further development, subject to successful planning permission, of a solar farm.\\n\u2022 Initial exploration and subsequent development, subject to feasibility study completion, of Project Genesis, a project to explore supply and \\ndemand of low cost, affordable heat at scale, recognising the opportunities presented by heat network expansion, heat zoning, energy storage \\nand fleet decarbonisation.\\n\u2022 Development and implementation of a pipeline of innovation projects exploring new technologies and proof of concepts. Trials will include \\nproduct development and piloting of residential and micro business solutions and propositions.\\n\u2022 Data, digital and connectivity will be a key enabler and theme across energy propositions",
