        "hazard": "Other: Extreme weather events",
        "vulnerableGroups": "Outdoor workers|Low-income households|Frontline workers|Children and youth|Elderly|Vulnerable health groups",
        "sectorsExposed": "Forestry|Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply|Agriculture|Transportation and storage|Waste management|Water supply",
        "impacts": "Extreme weather significantly impacts vulnerable groups and sectors of a city including but not limited to energy, transport, agriculture, water supply and waste management. Dundee City Council's CRVA noted that each of these sectors will 'likely' be impacted in some way or another at varying levels of intensity. For example, extreme weather events such as droughts, floods or storms impact food security; in the energy sector, extreme weather events disrupt service provision; transport systems face disruptions in the form floods and high winds; the supply of clean water can be compromised; and waste management faces challenges with damaged facilities, or the collection and disposal of waste. The impact to such a vast number of sectors undoubtably affects entire populations, where vulnerable population groups are generally more susceptible to climate hazards.",
        "populationExposed": "Data is not available",
        "currentProbability": "High",
