        "sectorsExposed": "Manufacturing|Education|Administrative and support service activities|Construction",
        "impacts": "Climate Change is likely to have a negative impact on air quality both directly and indirectly, as higher temperatures are likely to create atmospheric conditions favouring ozone formation. This causes risks to both air quality and health.",
