        "description": "Developed together with other Council departments, Hello Dundee, previously known as Hello Lamp Post, utilises an AI-integrated platform together with 100 physical signs with QR codes situated at various locations across the city for the community to engage with environmental and sustainability-related topics. The tool provides an informative resource at the community's fingertips. There are a total of eleven topics on the platform with key conversations covering electric vehicles, the Low Emission Zone and waste disposal.\\n\\nHello Dundee has seen a total of 22,095 interactions, under 9,188 conversations by 6,869 individual users since its launch.",
