        "comment": "All climate targets in Dundee are set based on direct or indirect engagement with Scottish Government. The Scottish Government may be referred as Provincial government in terms of Government level. The Tyndall Centre for Climate Change Research has advised that Dundee should reach zero or near-zero carbon no later than 2042 to align with the Paris Agreement's \u201cwell below 2\u00b0C and pursuing 1.5\u00b0C\u201d goal and associated equity principles. Dundee's city-wide target of net zero by 2045 is closely aligned with this recommendation, while the Council's organisational Net Zero Transition Plan sets a more ambitious goal of achieving net zero emissions by 2038, reflecting the Tyndall Centre's guidance."
