        "comment": "Local Heat Energy Efficiency Strategy (LHEES) Scottish Government officers group, coordinated by the Heat in Buildings Delivery Division within the Directorate of Energy and Climate Change, brings together officers from across Scottish Government, local authorities, and partner organisations to support the development and delivery of Local Heat and Energy Efficiency Strategies (LHEES). \\nThe group focuses on:\\n\u2022\\tReviewing guidance and methodology for LHEES development\\n\u2022\\tEvaluating stakeholder experiences through surveys and consultations\\n\u2022\\tSharing insights from capacity-building workshops delivered via Zero Waste Scotland\\n\u2022\\tCollaborating with delivery partners such as HNSU and Ramboll\\n\u2022\\tInforming future iterations of LHEES to better support heat decarbonisation, energy efficiency improvements, and efforts to tackle fuel poverty in Scotland\\n\\nThe forum also serves as a platform for continuous engagement with local authorities and key stakeholders, ensuring that LHEES evolves in response to practical experience and emerging needs.\\n"
