        "refId": "Mitigation Action 7",
        "sector": "Stationary energy: On-site renewable energy generation",
        "description": "Solar Together Essex is as a collective purchasing scheme to help residents and small businesses to purchase high quality solar panels at an affordable price and from trusted suppliers. The council has been running campaigns almost every year since 2018, with four schemes delivered as of June 2023. 305 installations were undertaken during the 2018 campaign, with an average size of 3.3kWp, resulting in production of 2,800kWh each per year. The 2021 campaign saw 508 installations, equating to 464 tonnes/CO2 reduction in year 1. The 2022 campaign delivered 648 solar PV installations, equating to 521 tonnes/CO2 reduction in year 1. In 2023, this scheme helped 699 residents source solar panels and battery storage. The scheme secures significant discounts (20 to 37%) for residents from reliable suppliers. The 2024 Solar Together scheme saw over 5,600 registrations of interest and 508 installs. Over 30 homes have also been retrofit with battery storage. The 2025 campaign is now underway and has seen nearly 3,000 registrations and over 400 households accept their offer. This demonstrates not only the huge demand for solar energy, but the continued interest in uptake of the scheme. Since the first scheme launched in August 2018, Solar Together Essex has delivered 2,752 solar PV installs on roofs in Essex. This will avoid in excess of 2,400 tonnes of CO2e annually and over 60,000 tonnes of CO2e across the 25-year lifespan.",
