        "comment": "Formal consultations and less formal engagement with district, borough, city and unitary councils on a range of transport-related strategies and plans including: development of local transport plan LTP4; Local Cycling and Walking Infrastructure Plans (LCWiPS - near complete coverage of Essex); development of new Essex Air Quality Strategy (currently in draft form) covering Greater Essex geography, which is strongly aligned with policy needed to deliver decarbonisation; On-Street Residential Chargepoint Scheme (ORCS) and Local Electric Vehicle Infrastructure (LEVI.) Also working with Essex Highways on their decarbonisation strategy covering service delivery: https://www.essexhighways.org/uploads/road-strategies/kd04-fp-005-01-24--a1-decarbonisation-strategy.pdf"
