        "mechanisms": "Capacity development|Reporting of climate and/or environmental data|Procurement|Project implementation and management|Technical assistance|Policy and regulation development/ implementation|Collaborative initiative|Funding (grants)|Circular economy business model support|Multi-jurisdictional regional collaboratives|Knowledge or data sharing",
        "focusAreas": "Food|Education|Emissions reduction|Waste",
        "description": "Waste Strategy for Essex \\n10-week public consultation facilitated by ECC on behalf of all thirteen members of the EWP providing residents, businesses and communities with an opportunity to have their say on the priorities and approaches proposed in the draft strategy. The findings of the consultation exercise were independently analysed and used by the EWP to develop the final strategy. Over the consultation period 4,545 responses were received from across the County. ECC also ran an extensive event programme and targeted focus group sessions for residents, community organisations and businesses. See https://www.loveessex.org/sites/default/files/4567776/2024-07/Waste%20Strategy%20for%20Essex.pdf for adopted strategy\\n\\nDevelopment of Shared Strategic Approach - Collaborative working with local government partners and communities to develop a shared approach to waste management with carbon reduction as a central pillar. The expansion of services to enhance resource efficiency through ECC funding of local partners recycling service provision\\n\\nExpansion of Recycling Services - worked collaboratively with local government partners and industry to expand the range of material collected for recycling and achieve enhanced carbon efficiency. This includes supporting the establishment of segregated food waste collections, enabling food to be used within anaerobic digestion facilities to generate renewable energy. \\n\\nBehavioural Change - The testing of innovative behavioural change activity in collaboration with local government partners and communities to increase participation in recycling services and the capture of materials for recycling \\n",
