        "focusAreas": "Energy|Public health|Education|Inclusive climate action and/or equity|Building and Infrastructure|Finance",
        "description": "The Climate Action Working Group of the Essex Anchors Network: the network brings together 'Anchor Institutions' - large, typically not-for-profit organisations like hospitals, local councils, and universities from across Essex - whose long-term sustainability is tied to the wellbeing of the populations they serve. ECC coordinates, supports and participates in the Climate Working Group, whose members work together to deliver net zero and green growth in Greater Essex. This sits under the umbrella of the Essex Partnership. In 2022, the group's focus was on short and long-term responses to fuel poverty and in 2023, the group focused on air quality, resulting in the creation of the Essex Air Quality Working Group. This group brings together local government and health sector partners to drive and support a system-wide approach to indoor and external air quality in Essex, to deliver improved health outcomes. in 2025, the Climate Action Working Group is supporting the development of the draft Essex Air Quality Strategy and the Local Area Energy Plan and is collaborating on a funding bid to roll out Healthy Streets around schools in Essex. ",
