        "description": "ECC has entered into a new contract for the treatment of residual waste, stopping the use of landfill and moving instead to the use of a local energy from waste plant. Under this contract, the use of landfill will stop in 2025, 5 years ahead of ithe target in the Waste Strategy. \\n\\nOver the initial 7 years of the contract the switch to energy from waste is expected to reduce greenhouse gas emissions from residual waste treatment by 30%, saving over 540,000 tonnes of carbon dioxide. \\n\\nCarbon limits and penalties for failure have also been incorporated within these contracts \\n",
