        "primaryEntity": "Civil society: Other: not for profit organisation",
        "mechanisms": "Cleaner production industry support|Financing (investment)|Technical assistance|Collaborative initiative|Funding (grants)|Capacity development",
        "focusAreas": "Energy|Emissions reduction|Finance|Resilience",
        "description": "In February 2024, the Essex Net Zero Delivery Taskforce (ECC's EssNet project) secured further support from Innovate UK's Net Zero Living Programme to pilot its innovative business model featuring the installation of solar and PV battery across a joined-up network of domestic and commercial roofs. EssNet aims to remove barriers around data, finance and technical coordination which prevent communities realising their energy generation and storage ambitions. The project has launched a not-for-profit delivery vehicle, Essex Community Energy CIC (ECE CIC), to deliver services to communities across Essex and beyond, supplying the technical and financial expertise and support needed to bring forward large scale, high impact place-based projects. ECE CIC will aggregate installation opportunities into investable-scale projects, secure that investment and provide the technical and organisational structures to help communities realise their decarbonisation and energy security goals. EssNet is delivered in partnership with UK Community Works CIC, Power Circle Projects Ltd and UK Power Networks and sits alongside Essex County Council's established community energy support programme, providing one possible solution to the county realising its sustainability ambitions",
        "otherEntities": "National government|Energy|Utilities|Local government within country/area"
