        "focusAreas": "Emissions reduction|Resilience|Energy|Inclusive climate action and/or equity",
        "description": "The Jaywick and District Energy Hub was developed through a year-long community engagement process led by Essex County Council and supported by the EU-funded Shared Green Deal Project. The Hub aims to help residents make their homes warmer, reduce energy bills and improve health and wellbeing by providing advice and support on home energy efficiency, grant funding, DIY measures, income maximisation and debt management. Essex County Council is working in partnership with Citizens Advice Tendring/Chelmsford and Tendring District Council on this project, and the Hub is staffed by advisers from both of these organisations and by a community energy champion from Jaywick Sands. The Hub opened on August 27, 2024, and by the end of July 2025 it had supported 180 clients, reaching 250 residents including almost 100 children. Clients have benefited from more than \u00a315,000 of direct financial support (fuel and food vouchers) and have been supported to apply for more than \u00a3300,000 in unclaimed benefits. 43 home visits have been carried out and 54 clients have been referred to the Eco4 grant scheme for home insulation/renewable energy.",
        "otherEntities": "NGO and associations|Residents/community groups|Other: Citizens Advice|Local government within country/area"
