        "mechanisms": "Collaborative initiative|Capacity development|Funding (grants)",
        "focusAreas": "Emissions reduction|Transport (Mobility)",
        "description": "Launched in 2021, Essex Pedal Power is a community cycling initiative, which operates in Clacton & Jaywick Sands, Harwich & Dovercourt, Colchester, Basildon, Canvey Island and Harlow where over 4000 bikes have been provided. The programme provides free bikes, volunteer opportunities, and training sessions to local people living in some of the county's most disadvantaged communities to :\\n\u2022\\tIncrease cycling participation\\n\u2022\\tImprove the health and wellbeing of local people\\n\u2022\\tIncrease sustainable travel through cycling\\n\u2022\\tIncrease employability and improve the local economy\\n\u2022\\tCreate resilience and connectedness in local communities\\n\\nAn independent evaluation of free bike schemes across the country, including Essex Pedal Power, carried out by Volterra demonstrates strong impact with a social return on Investment calculated at \u00a311.80 per \u00a31 spent,. The evaluation found that free bike schemes are cost-effective in delivering economic, social, and environmental benefits.\\n\u2022\\tFree bike schemes save the NHS >\u00a31 million per year through reduced cases of premature death and non-communicable diseases.\\n\u2022\\tFree bikes schemes have resulted in over 7 million car kilometres saved.\\n\u2022\\tEssex Pedal Power in Clacton & Jaywick recorded the highest increased trips to employment areas.\\n",
