        "refId": "Mitigation Action 1",
        "sector": "Stationary energy: On-site renewable energy generation",
        "description": "The GCC Solar PV project phase 1 is part of a wider solar PV programme that aims to install solar electricity generation capability at all GCC locations where it is feasible and cost effective. Phase 1 has now concluded. Locations were initially assessed on roof type and orientation with first pass feasibility studies being performed to assess energy demand of the building, potential for electricity generation and local grid conditions. The feasibility studies also provided a proposed array size and cost benefit analysis for each location. The project was part funded by GCC Capital and a Salix Energy Efficiency Loans Scheme. The project delivered eight solar PV arrays with a collective size of 992 kWp and a generation capacity of 700,000 kWh annually. This represents annual fiscal savings of approximately 182,000 with a project payback period of seven years.\\n\\nFor GCC Solar PV project phase 2, detailed feasibility studies have also been undertaken at a further 38 GCC properties. The locations comprise a variety of service areas including a mix of Education, HSCP, NRS and Glasgow life locations. It is estimated that these locations could contribute approximately a further 4 MWp of solar generation and represent a considerable increase in PV generation capacity across the Glasgow Council building estate. Upon completion these have the potential to deliver almost 3.2 GWh of electricity per annum saving over 715 tCO2e. At current electricity prices this equates to over \u00a3830k in annual savings with higher savings expected in the event of rises in the cost of grid-supplied electricity.",
        "status": "2023",
        "cobenefits": "2051 or later",
        "financeStatus": "Estimated annual renewable energy generated due to action|Estimated reduction in annual inventory emissions due to action",
        "totalCost": null,
        "emissionsSaved": null
