        "description": "Glasgow City Council is a participating member of the UK Circular Cities and Regions Network. Lead by ReLondon, the UK Circular Cities and Regions Network is a network of circular economy officers from local authorities across the UK that aims to promote knowledge sharing and collaboration. The network holds regular meetings/webinars where officers share lessons learnt from local circular programmes and activities alongside presentations from relevant external organisations with the aim to exchange knowledge between local authorities in the UK to improve waste and resource management and accelerate the circular economy transition.",
