        "description": "Glasgow City Council has worked with the Ellen MacArthur Foundation (EMF), a non-profit organisation that creates evidence-based research on the benefits of a circular economy, and how it can contribute to solving global challenges like climate change and biodiversity loss. EMF supports cities across the world to the transition to a circular economy. Led by EMF, Glasgow City Council participates in the Global Circular Cities Stand-Up, a network aimed at sharing knowledge and updates between cities globally with the aim to accelerate the transition to circular cities. Glasgow City Council has also worked with the EMF on a critical review of Glasgow's Circular Economy Route Map.",
