        "description": "The Mayor of London secured central government funding for London under the Home Upgrade Grant 2 scheme. The Greater London Authority will run the programme, which is owned by the Department for Energy Security and Net Zero (DESNZ) during 2024 and early 2025. The programme is specifically targeted at low income households whose homes have a low Energy Performance Certificate (EPC) and are not connected to the gas grid. As with earlier schemes, there are a range of potential energy saving measures that may be fitted to qualifying homes, such as: heat pumps; insulation for walls, lofts and floors; draughtproofing; solar photo voltaic installations",
