        "sector": "Stationary energy: Increase use of clean energy sources for heating and cooling buildings",
        "description": "The Local Energy Accelerator (LEA) extended and expanded the work started by the Decentralised Energy Enabling Project, from October 2020 to end July 2024. LEA funded feasibility and development plans for clean, locally generated energy projects, maximising carbon savings and contributing to London's climate emergency response. LEA will cut carbon emissions by thousands of tonnes per year through enabling the development of distributed, flexible, resilient and low carbon heat and power resources such as low carbon heat networks. LEA funded expertise for all stages of low carbon, decentralised energy project development from feasibility to commercialisation work. It helped the public and previously the private sector to build the business case and provide the expertise they need to deliver more local distributed energy across London. More info at: www.london.gov.uk/lea",
        "status": "2020.0",
        "cobenefits": "2051 or later",
