        "description": "In May 2021 the Mayor established, the Greater Manchester Retrofit Task Force which is leading on a three-year programme that aims to tackle the climate crisis through innovative finance solutions and building the supply and demand for the skills and jobs needed to grow the supply chain. The Task Force brings together industry, academia, NGO's, financiers and the public sector. Through successful collaboration the Task Force partners launched the Retrofit Action Plan which focuses on three streams of work, delivery, finance and skills. Since the launch of the plan significant progress has been made contractors have now been procured to deliver Your, Homes Better a service for residents across GM to access advice on retrofit measure they can install in there homes and a new Retrofit Skills Hub has also been established, offering courses to upskill into green jobs and training to get more people working on renovation projects and boost the skills and talent pipeline.",
