        "description": "The Energy Innovation Agency was set up to accelerate the energy transition towards a carbon-neutral economy by bridging the innovation gap through increasing the deployment of innovative energy solutions in Greater Manchester. The agency is a partnership between GMCA, Bruntwood, Growth Company, Hitachi, Manchester Metropolitan University, SSE, University of Manchester and University of Salford. It cuts across, public, commercial, businesses, technology, academia and energy services. https://www.energyinnovationagency.co.uk/",
