        "refId": "Mitigation Action 14",
        "sector": "Transportation: Electric vehicle charging points and infrastructure",
        "description": "https://www.lbhf.gov.uk/transport-and-roads/electric-vehicles The council has delivered one of the densest networks of electric vehicle charging points in the country, with 2,800 charging points and all homes and offices now within 400m of a charging point. Local registration of electric vehicles is increasing exponentially, increasing from 3,861 to 6,453 between 2022 and 2023 alone. The borough has also become home to one of the first filling stations to be converted to all electric charging: https://www.lbhf.gov.uk/articles/news/2022/01/fulham-now-home-world-s-first-shell-ev-charging-hub",
