        "engagementPurpose": "To facilitate capacity building across different levels of government|To facilitate information sharing across different levels of government",
        "comment": "https://www.londoncouncils.gov.uk/our-shared-ambitions/tackling-climate-change. London boroughs have signed up to collective climate targets in a Joint Statement on Climate Change agreed by the London-wide Transport and Environment Committee in 2019. This established seven climate programmes through which London boroughs collaborate on knowledge sharing, capacity building, and project delivery. Hammersmith & Fulham plays a leading role in one of these programmes, the One World Living (OWL) programme, which is focused on cutting consumption-based emissions and promoting a circular economy across London. As well as being the leading borough for OWL's electricals work, Hammersmith & Fulham contributes to other OWL workstreams, such as the single-use plastics working group. In April 2025 we became one of the first boroughs to sign the Single-use Plastics Pledge, which we helped to co-develop alongside London Councils and other London boroughs. Signing the pledge was a commitment within H&F's Plastic Free Policy Refresh, which we adopted in March 2025 to eliminate non-essential single-use plastics from our operations and work with local stakeholders to facilitate a reduction borough-wide."
