        "description": "Kirklees Council is working in partnership with the West Yorkshire Combined Authority and One Community to offer grants to community groups to support climate-friendly projects. The total awarded grant pot is just under \u00a3280,000 awarded to projects that prioritize:\\n\\nLocal, clean, and flexible energy solutions, Healthy, affordable, and efficient buildings, Walking, cycling, and public transport, Green and climate-ready nature solutions. A total of \u00a3229,928 of the fund was spent on energy efficiency improvements that will improve sustainable energy in community buildings promote local clean and flexible energy solutions. This will improve community buildings that support disadvantaged community members. A total of \u00a315,570 was spent to fund the development of active travel provision with a focus on deprived areas in Kirklees. A total of \u00a334,353 was allocated to improvements to the natural environment and nature based solutions and biodiversity throughout Kirklees. This will create space for the community to enjoy and grow a nature based space and achieves green and climate ready nature solutions. For more information about the climate grants, please see the following link: https://www.kirklees.gov.uk/beta/climate-emergency/community-grants.aspx",
