        "impacts": "Increasing temperatures are expected to become a challenge for Newcastle as a result of climate change. We will use the Heatwave Plan for England to prepare for, alert people to, and prevent, the major avoidable effects on health during periods of severe heat in England. The most vulnerable parts of the population to heat stress will be elderly and clinically vulnerable patients. A key focus will be on managing the impact and acute health needs on those groups in particular. The UK has experienced it's top ten hottest years since 2002, with June 2023 recorded as the hottest on record. In Newcastle temperature's reached 37 degrees Celsius in July 2022. Particularly vulnerable sectors include agriculture from potential crop failure, the electricity and gas supply network due to the effect of extreme heat on infrastructure and the health and social sector due to the increase in the number of people requiring medical assistance.",
