        "sector": "Transportation: Electric vehicle charging points and infrastructure",
        "description": "In March 2024, the Council released our Electric Vehicle Charging Strategy for Newcastle. This strategy has been developed to respond to the current and expected future need for EV charging infrastructure across the city. The strategy sets how Newcastle City Council will support increasing uptake of electric vehicles on roads across the city. To date we have installed over 90 charge points in the city. Roll out will include residential neighbourhood charging, publicly available destination charging points, an EV car club model, fleet transition and charging infrastructure for electric taxis. We have been successful in a joint bid for Local Electric Vehicle Infrastructure Charging with Transport North East of \u00a315.829 million.",
