        "description": "Newcastle City Council has joined four other local authorities across the UK in piloting the FPF FlexCollect project. From June 2023, 5,000 homes have been able to recycle flexible plastics such as plastic bags, wrappers, packets, and film, which are currently some of the hardest items to recycle. Around two in five households in the area are said to use the service and to date so far, the council said it has collected over 51,000 bags of flexible plastic packaging for recycling. This trial expanded to a further 35,000 homes in Newcastle in October 2024 ahead of mandatory collections in 2027.",
