        "renewableTarget": "We have modelled the 'Net Zero Newcastle - 2030 Action Plan' on the basis of achieving city-wide Net Zero by 2030 which delivers a carbon abatement curve well in advance of the 1.5oC climate scenario based on mitigation actions. However, for adaptation, we recognise the need to plan for higher climate scenarios (2oC and 4oC), and as such our city wide resilience assessments, flood risk planning, heatwave planning, cold weather planning, etc are all taking into account three scenarios (1.5oC, 2oC and 4oC).",
