        "comment": "The authority has been engaging with government to secure Salix Public Sector Decarbonisation Scheme grant. PSDS grant scheme was made available for capital energy efficiency and the heat decarbonisation projects within the public sector for non-domestic buildings. The schemes that were successfully awarded grant in Round 1 of the scheme were to supplement existing gas boilers with less polluting energy efficient electric heating systems by way of air source heap pumps, thereby reducing the carbon output of the four buildings identified. This project supports the work of the Climate Emergency Board and the Climate Emergency Action Plan, specifically the strategic aims of improving Energy Efficiency & Decarbonising heat. The grant scheme will deliver stimulus to the energy efficiency and low carbon heat sector and deliver significant carbon savings. The grant of \u00a33.289m was awarded to the Authority. The Authority subsequently bid into the Public Sector Decarbonisation Scheme (PSDS) Phase 3c to reduce carbon emissions within the Authorities public buildings estate. The objective of the Phase 3c application was to support the transition to low carbon heating in public sector buildings, in addition to improving energy efficiency. It aims to achieve this by providing funding to replace end-of-life fossil fuel systems (gas boilers) with low carbon heat sources as a requirement and bundled with energy efficiency measures to facilitate a 'whole building' approach to heat decarbonisation. In 2023/24 the Authority was successful in its submission and are in receipt of a grant offer of \u00a31,128,557.00 with the match contribution for projects being met by the Authority. An opportunity has now arisen to bid to the Salix Low Carbon Skills Fund to enable survey work to be undertaken to provide information on options that may be available to reduce carbon emissions within the Authority public buildings and schools estate. On 20 March 2024, the Department for Energy Security and Net Zero announced a \u00a316 million of funding for public sector organisations to engage specialist and expert advice and skills to develop detailed project proposals to help applications for future grant funding for capital decarbonisation measures, or alternative sources of finance. Undertaking additional upfront design work should mean future applications represent improved Value For Money and put the Authority in a strong position for future funding opportunities. The LCSF scheme is 100% funded with no match funding required. The Authority is currently awaiting the outcome on this.\\n\\nIn 2024/25 the Authority was awarded \u00a32.912m of PSDS grant which will be used to replace existing gas fired boilers in two buildings with air source heat pumps. In addition to the air source heat pumps, a range of ancillary systems and equipment will be upgraded to ensure the building management systems are fully optimised. Solar PV will feature on one building to reduce the requirement of grid electricity to power the heat pumps. The works are expected to save 252 tCO2e across both sites.\\n"
