        "description": "The Management Plan is the most \\nimportant document that the National \\nPark Authority produces. It sets out a \\nlong-term vision for the National Park (the entire area, not just the land that is owned by the Authority) and describes the objectives, policies and goals that the National Park Authority, other public bodies and stakeholders will pursue to achieve it. The Management Plan highlights the key priorities for action over the next twenty years to help address the challenges that the National Park will face. The current plan is adopted and is in operation from 2022-2027.\\n\\nThe plan is adopted by the Authority's Members and is available to the public on the Authority's website. The Authority reports on the progress made towards the plan's outcomes in the annual monitoring statement, which is subject to public scrutiny by Members and is published on the Authority's website once adopted. The annual monitoring statement for 2025 will be put to members in December 2025.",
