        "impacts": "Coastal flooding poses significant risks to various vulnerable groups and sectors:\\n\\nSocial Vulnerabilities: Elderly, low-income, and minority communities face heightened risks due to higher likelihood that they will experience limited mobility, financial constraints, and reduced capacity to respond or recover. Mental health impacts and pressure on social services may increase.\\n\\nOccupational Risks: Outdoor and frontline workers are exposed to hazardous conditions and increased service demands.\\n\\nEconomic Disruption: Industries such as fishing, construction, and real estate may suffer due to infrastructure damage, delays, and reduced activity in high-risk areas.\\n\\nEnvironmental Threats: Waste management sites and conservation areas are at risk of contamination and degradation.\\n\\nInfrastructure Impact: Flooding can disrupt transportation, storage, and educational facilities, affecting service delivery and learning continuity.\\n",
