        "impacts": "Urban Flooding Impacts\\n\\nVulnerable Populations: Elderly and those with health conditions are at greater risk due to mobility issues, health complications (e.g. hypothermia), and limited access to care or medication. Children and youth may suffer mental health impacts and educational disruption.\\n\\nWorkforce Impacts: Frontline and outdoor workers face hazardous conditions and increased workloads, potentially leading to service interruptions.\\n\\nSocial Inequities: Low-income and marginalised communities may struggle to recover financially and access essential services post-flooding.\\n\\nInfrastructure Risks: Flooding can damage energy, communication, water, sewerage, and waste systems, leading to service outages and environmental contamination.\\n\\nEducation Disruption: Damage to schools can affect learning and development.\\n\\nEconomic Consequences: Logistics, wholesale trade, and real estate may be disrupted. Insurance and financial services may face surges in claims. Property values may decline.\\n\\nHealth and Social Care: Flooded facilities and staff shortages can hinder healthcare and social service delivery.\\n",
