        "sector": "Stationary energy: Energy efficiency/ retrofit measures addressing existing commercial, residential and/or municipal buildings",
        "description": "The council is working to deliver a programme of retrofit activity on council owned homes. This is a significant area of work following the award of over \u00a321m by the department of Energy Security and net Zero under the Warm Homes Social Housing Fund. This programme has a match funding contribution, and the council have committed ~\u00a318m into this programme of retrofit, demonstrating the ambition of the council to support housing decarbonisation. It is estimated this will retrofit over 2000 homes in the next 3 years. \\n\\nNYC also provide support to private residents to retrofit their homes. HUG2 delivered retrofit measures into over 330 homes off gas homes, saving residents approximately \u00a3770 per year per property. The success of this programme has positioned the council in a strong position to deliver the Warm Homes Local Grant scheme, which provided NYC with over \u00a35.9m to support retrofit to private residents. This scheme has recently launched and is expected to support retrofit on nearly 250 homes. \\n",
