        "sector": "Stationary energy: Energy efficiency/ retrofit measures addressing existing commercial, residential and/or municipal buildings",
        "description": "North Yorkshire Council York and North Yorkshire Combined Authority have been selected by the Department of Energy Security and Net Zero (DESNZ) to be one of three pilot places within the Local Net Zero Accelerator Programme. The Programme seeks to test different delivery models to accelerate the move towards net zero, at a local level, by leveraging in commercial investment at scale through a bundled approach. As a delivery partner North Yorkshire are a key partner in this project and are to receive an allocation of funding for our time and support provided. The overarching aim of the York and North Yorkshire pilot is to test the replicability of Bristol's City Leap (Strategic Energy Partnership) programme in a different locality, and whether it is possible with significantly reduced time and costs of development. The specific objectives of the pilot are: \\n- To identify and agree the key outcomes and success criteria for a Strategic Energy Partnership replicator in York and North Yorkshire. \\n- To identify the key requirements to replicate the Bristol model and test whether the model is the most appropriate strategic energy partnership model for York and North Yorkshire -- To adapt the Strategic Energy Partnership model to a Y&NY context, or if the model is not suitable co-design an alternative partnership model that can drive investment and increase pace of delivery of net zero in the region.\\n- To develop an Action Plan to identify key activities, resources and costs to implement a Strategic Energy Partnership at an accelerated pace in Y&NY, or for an alternative preferred energy partnership model for the region.",
