        "refId": "Mitigation Action 3",
        "sector": "Transportation: Electric vehicle charging points and infrastructure",
        "description": "As of August 2024, NCC has over 300 individual charging sockets in operation across the county. Wider availability of charge points can facilitate uptake of EVs. \\nNCC will continue to install EV vehicle infrastructure and access available funding streams. NCC will select locations in collaboration with communities to remove barriers to EV ownership. \\nNCC are planning updates on the existing EV strategy. \\nExisting strategy - https://northumberland.moderngov.co.uk/documents/s11009/05%20Electric%20Vehicle%20Charging%20Strategy%202022-25.pdf",
        "status": "2020",
        "cobenefits": "End year not known/not applicable",
