        "mechanisms": "Collaborative initiative",
        "focusAreas": "Energy",
        "description": "NCC collaborated with the North East Combined Authority and other regional local authorities to secure funding from the Department of Energy Security and Net Zero for additional in-person support for more vulnerable households, or properties that are more complex to decarbonise. This project supplemented the establishment of an online and telephone based one-stop-shop energy advice service for residents that was funded through UK Shared Prosperity Fund.\\n\\nNCC also collaborates with the North East Combined Authority and other regional local authorities to deliver the investment priorities included in the North East Deeper Devolution Deal, these include but are not limited to significant growth sectors such as offshore wind, and partnerships including the North East Strategic Energy Board, and the Environment, Coast and Rural Taskforce.\\n\\n\\nNCC also collaborates with regional local authorities in England and Scotland through the Borderlands Inclusive Growth Deal. The Borderlands Energy Programme has developed initial energy masterplanning for the region, and has established an Energy Investment Programme to support the delivery of low carbon, inclusive growth.",
