        "focusAreas": "Resilience|Emissions reduction|Agriculture",
        "description": "There is currently no statutory requirement for local authorities to support farmers or land based sectors to transition to net zero. Northumberland is a vast rural county and in 2022 NCC undertook an inquiry titled 'The Future of Farming' to better understand the challenges and opportunities faced by farmers and landowners in Northumberland. This led to NCC securing funding for a project in collaboration with Northumberland's Rural Design Centre. The project 'Farming in a Changing Climate' aims to better understand the role of the Local Authority in supporting farmers to decarbonise. This was funded through the Innovate UK Net Zero Fast Followers programme. The project concluded in July 2025 and NCC is developing the findings from these projects into a useful offer for farmers aiming to reduce emissions and enhance biodiversity on their land. In addition to this, the Northumberland Small Business Service supports a Farming Advisory Service delivered through the Northumberland National Park which supported farmers to undertake carbon audits and the Farming Officer Network in Northumberland has been established to share best practice for groups that provide support to farmers for example by organising site visits and ensuring messages to farmers in the region are consistent.",
        "otherEntities": "Agriculture|Industry trade group|Residents/community groups|Food & Beverage"
