        "impacts": "Internal flooding of properties occurs at least once per year somewhere within the city, typically caused by flash or surface flooding resulting from torrential rain. These events can be highly localised, meaning that flooding could occur in various parts of the city. \\n\\nThe number of people affected by flooding can vary significantly from year to year\u2014ranging from fewer than 10 individuals in some instances to over 100 in others. While it is difficult to quantify the exact financial losses, they are likely to be considerable, particularly when residents are forced to move out of their homes for several months while repairs are made. \\n\\nFlooding also presents challenges with (re)insurance, and evidence suggests that it can lead to prolonged psychological and mental health impacts for those affected. However, there is currently no local data to confirm these effects within Nottingham. \\n\\nAdditionally, there may be unforeseen indirect impacts on vulnerable populations who are not directly flooded, highlighting the broader societal risks posed by such events.",
