        "impacts": "Nottingham is expected to experience greater seasonality in rainfall patterns, with projections indicating more rainfall in winter and less in summer compared to the baseline average (1981-2000). \\n\\nKey Impacts on Water Availability\\n\\n Reduced Summer Water Availability: Declines in summer rainfall may result in increased water shortages, affecting the supply for various services, facilities, and communities across Nottingham. \\n\\nRegional Water Stress: Recent years have seen prolonged periods of hot weather combined with shorter rainfall seasons, creating significant regional water stress. \\n\\nWarmer weather has led to a surge in water usage, further exacerbating the strain on available water resources. \\n\\nThese changes highlight the importance of implementing sustainable water management strategies to address the challenges posed by shifting rainfall patterns and ensure the resilience of Nottingham's water supply.",
