        "sector": "Agriculture, Forestry and Land Use: Green space and/ or biodiversity preservation and expansion",
        "description": "Nottingham City Council continues to advance its ambitious tree planting programme, originally launched in the 2019/20 season with a target of planting 50,000 trees by 2023. As of late 2024, approximately 39,000 trees have been planted across the city. The Nottingham Green Guardians, a volunteer initiative under the Council's Parks Team, remain central to this effort, supporting tree planting across over 250 parks and open spaces. The 2024/25 planting season includes plans for additional Miyawaki-style forests, contributing to urban biodiversity and carbon sequestration. Once mature, the trees planted are expected to sequester approximately 1,050 tCO\u2082 annually, based on an average of 21 kg CO\u2082 per tree. This initiative supports Nottingham's commitment to becoming the UK's first carbon-neutral city by 2028.",
