        "sector": "Stationary energy: On-site renewable energy generation",
        "description": "CleanMobilEnergy is an Interreg NWE and Innovate UK funded project. NCC is delivering a City Pilot demonstrator as part of the wider project. The pilot will install innovative 'vehicle to grid' (V2G) bi-directional electric vehicle charging at Eastcroft Depot, solar PV and battery energy storage systems (BESS). The demonstrator aims to maximize the use of locally generated renewable generation (Solar PV) to cut the carbon emissions and costs associated with charging electric fleet vehicles, as well as reducing peak demand by using vehicles for short-term storage, alongside the BESS. The project has been running since September 2017 and aims to be fully operational by December 2025.",
