        "refId": "Mitigation Action 8",
        "sector": "Transportation: Other: Range of actions including: improve fuel economy and reduce CO2 emissions from bus, light rail (trams), motorized vehicles; improve public, active and micro mobility transport infrastructure, services and operations; procure electric vehicles.",
        "description": "Nottingham's Carbon Neutral Action Plan includes a range of actions to reduce emissions associated with private transport in the city. This includes actions around the key objectives to: - reduce the need to travel within the City; - encourage and enable more walking and cycling; - improve the quality and availability of low carbon public transport; - improve low carbon transport infrastructure; - moving away from internal combustion vehicles to ULEV such as electric or hydrogen vehicles. As of March 2025, Nottingham City Council's fleet comprises 486 vehicles, of which 210 are battery electric vehicles (BEVs), representing 43.21% of the total fleet. The transition to electric mobility reflects the Council's commitment to reducing Scope 1 and 2 emissions. A comparative analysis of fuel use shows that replacing diesel with Hydrotreated Vegetable Oil (HVO) would reduce emissions from 2,822.75 tCO\u2082e to 105.62 tCO\u2082e, resulting in a carbon saving of 2,717.12 tCO\u2082e. This shift supports the Council's broader carbon neutrality goals. Further details on specific actions for each objective are included at: https://www.nottinghamcity.gov.uk/media/2619917/2028-carbon-neutral-action-plan-v2-160620.pdf Nottingham's annual reviews of the action plan are published at: https://www.nottinghamcity.gov.uk/your-council/about-the-council/carbon-neutral-nottingham-2028/why-do-we-need-to-act/ The total estimated annual emissions reductions captures if all these actions were delivered, and currently known/anticipated local and national policy is delivered. The estimate also includes interdependencies with other actions, estimated in the same way, for example related to grid decarbonisation. To avoid double counting, specific transport actions as captured separately within this question have been subtracted from the total estimate emissions relating to all our actions related to transport. Some of these actions are reliant on funding that is not yet secured or significant Government action in all areas, including planning, legislation, policy and regulation.",
