        "description": "Nottingham's Carbon Neutral Action Plan includes a range of actions to reduce emissions associated existing domestic buildings. This includes actions around the key objectives to:\\n- Heating our buildings with low carbon and/or renewable heating and changing behaviours towards energy consumption\\n- Monitoring and encouraging energy efficiency standards and improvements\\n- Increasing the adoption of energy efficiency technologies and low-cost solutions in both commercial and domestic buildings\\n\\nFurther details on specific actions for each objective are included at https://www.nottinghamcity.gov.uk/media/2619917/2028-carbon-neutral-action-plan-v2-160620.pdf\\nNottingham's annual reviews of the action plan are published at: https://www.nottinghamcity.gov.uk/your-council/about-the-council/carbon-neutral-nottingham-2028/why-do-we-need-to-act/\\n\\nThe total estimated annual emissions reductions captures these if all these actions were delivered, and currently known/anticipated local and national policy is delivered. The estimate also includes interdependencies with other actions, estimated in the same way, for example related to grid decarbonisation. To avoid double counting, specific retrofit actions as captured separately within this question have been subtracted from the total estimate emissions relating to all our actions related to the existing domestic building stock. Some of these actions are reliant on funding that is not yet secured or significant Government action in all areas, including planning, legislation, policy and regulation.",
