        "engagementPurpose": "To facilitate the integration of this component into assessments and policy developed across different levels of government|To collect data and/or feedback from other levels of government to inform its development|To facilitate information sharing across different levels of government",
        "comment": "Nottingham is actively engaged in national and regional collaborations to drive forward climate action, ensuring that its efforts are aligned with broader goals across the UK. As part of the UK Core Cities Network, Nottingham works closely with other major cities such as Belfast, Birmingham, Bristol, Cardiff, Glasgow, Leeds, Liverpool, Manchester, Newcastle, and Sheffield. This collective advocacy group holds regular consultations and briefings with central government departments, focusing on carbon neutral and net zero strategies, while addressing key climate components measured by the CDP (Carbon Disclosure Project).\\n\\nThrough these interactions, Nottingham shares valuable insights and experiences with fellow cities, enabling the exchange of best practices around climate action. The Core Cities Network also advocates for stronger national-level policies and greater government action to address the climate crisis, amplifying Nottingham's voice on the national stage and ensuring that local initiatives receive the support they need.\\n\\nIn addition to national cooperation, Nottingham collaborates with local authorities across the region through partnerships such as the Midlands Net Zero Hub. This regional collaboration strengthens efforts by pooling resources, expertise, and strategies to accelerate the transition to a low-carbon economy. By participating in these regional and national networks, Nottingham is able to take a leadership role in driving climate action while benefiting from the collective knowledge and experience of other local authorities.\\n\\nThese partnerships not only reinforce Nottingham's commitment to achieving carbon neutrality but also ensure that the city remains at the forefront of innovative climate solutions, benefiting both its residents and the wider region."
