        "planType": "Standalone mitigation plan",
        "planName": "Zero Carbon Oxford Partnership 2040 Net Zero Roadmap and Action Plan https://zerocarbonoxford.org/roadmap-and-action-plans/",
        "yearAdopted": null,
        "scope": "Same (jurisdiction-wide) - covers entire jurisdiction and nothing else",
        "sectors": "Monitoring: Information on progress of plan is monitored and publicly reported annually or more frequently than annually|Evaluation: Evaluation of plan takes place every 3-5 years|Update: Updates to the plan are published every 3-5 years",
        "renewableTarget": "The action plan sets out an ambitious net-zero scenario. It features a 1.5\u00b0C aligned Science Based Target for all emission sources covered within the Basic+ reporting level of the Global Protocol for Community-Scale Greenhouse Gas Emission Inventories (GPC), and any remaining hard-to-decarbonise emissions can be compensated with certified greenhouse gas removal (GGR). This aligns the definition for a net-zero city or region with the SBTi's definition for a net-zero company. Therefore, the updated scenario is compared against a 1.5\u00b0C aligned Science Based Target to ensure that it is on track to meet this definition.The overall aim of the scenario is to describe a potential decarbonisation pathway and identify the near, medium and long-term actions needed to put Oxford on track to achieving net-zero carbon emissions by 2040. The scenario also provides a framework to:\u2022 Inform the Zero Carbon Oxford Partnership of the scale of decarbonisation that must be achieved across all GHG emission sources;\u2022 Provide evidence to support robust decision-making processes; and\u2022 Inspire radical action from partners.",
