        "description": "Two round of Knowledge Exchange funding in collaboration with University of Sheffield, working on researching best practise in Resist-Accept-Direct (RAD) adaptive land management methods, and communicating this to PDNPA leadership team. Subsequently working with stakeholders to develop recommendations for developing participatory decision making processes in RAD management. Resulted in recommendations for the next management plan development process, and a policy briefing is in progress.",
        "otherEntities": "Agriculture|Residents/community groups"
