        "impacts": "2/3 years ago with increasing rain fall Perth and Kinross was exposed large amounts of flooding in certain areas. Almondbank, Perth, and other areas. This has resulted in large capital investment in flood defences in certain areas. Works including; building up lands, creating flood plains and numerous pumping stations set up across Perth and Kinross area. \\n\\nThe increased likelihood of storms due to climate change has resulted in increased damage to bridges and pipelines, with high river flows thought to be contributing to this. Several key bridges in Perth and Kinross that connect large sections of the population have been identified as high scour risk.\\n\\nFurthermore, warmer temperatures may be accelerating weathering-related deterioration for embankments. Risks to infrastructure services from river flooding such as railway lines and stations.",
