        "description": "The Perth & Kinross Climate Action Hub enables communities to take effective climate action across Perth and Kinross.\\nThe Hub is supported by a collaboration of\\norganisations to ensure it benefits from the breadth of experience in the area. Climate Cafe is the anchor organisation for the Perth & Kinross\\nClimate Action Hub. The Hub allows local community organisations to do what they do and more by reducing the information down to a manageable understandable format. Making\\nthem more efficient and allowing for collaboration through engagement and networking. This has the added benefit of reducing duplication and maximising the benefits from funding to the local communities. Allowing Perth and Kinross to\\nengage with one collective voice, allowing all rural areas to be represented via the\\nCommunity Climate Champions. It is clear that there is not huge awareness about what existing opportunities for resources, support and funding may be out there for example in public bodies, to\\nsupport current action. The Hub is a conduit to signpost information, resources, support and funding for opportunities directly to communities - rather than through agencies or third parties. \\nThe Hub was successful in receiving funding from the Scottish Government in order to be developed. Perth and Kinross Council supported their funding application with a support letter to the Scottish Government and has been engaging with the Hub since its development.",
