        "impacts": "Reading benefits from an excellent record of local weather observations dating from 1902, gathered by the University of Reading. Just from this record, it is possible to see indications of changes in climate. For example, the six warmest summers recorded in Reading all occurred since 1976 (with 2018 the warmest), while the five coldest summers all occurred before 1955. Since 1961, mean temperature in Reading has been rising at a rate of 0.26 \u00b0C per decade (J. Lowe, pers. com, 2019).June 1976 was the warmest June on record in Reading, until 2025 where the temperature exceeded the previous mean temperature record of 18.1 \u00b0C, at 18.3 \u00b0C (3 \u00b0C above the June average for 1981-2010). Like 1976, the very hot weather continued into July. After a dry start to the year, the hot dry conditions led to widespread forest and woodland fires in Berkshire (and many other places in south and south-east England). Maximum temperatures reached 30 \u00b0C or above every day for 14 days from end of June into July 1976, peaking at 34.0 \u00b0C on 26 June. Following a very hot summer in 2018, which saw temperatures in Reading reach a high of 32.9\u00b0C, with seven hot days where the temperature reached 30\u00baC or over, Reading also experienced record-breaking temperatures during 2019. Between 1908 and 2021, only five days have reached 35 \u00b0C or higher in Reading. The hottest day recorded in Reading was 36.4 \u00b0C on 10 August 2003 until a new (provisional) high of 37.6 \u00b0C was recorded at the University of Reading on 19 July 2022 during the heatwave which saw the UK national temperature record also broken. Looking ahead, hot summers are expected to become more common. In the recent past (1981-2000) the chance of a summer as hot as 2018 (one of the hottest on record) was less than 10%. The chance has already increased due to climate change and is now between 10% and 25%. With future warming, the chance of a summer as hot as 2018 is around 50% by mid-century. 2025 has so far proven to be the warmest summer on record in the UK.",
