        "refId": "Mitigation Action 4",
        "sector": "Stationary energy: Other: Urban tree planting",
        "description": "Under the Council's Trees Strategy adopted in 2021 (see https://democracy.reading.gov.uk/documents/s21657/12%20Rewilding%20March%202022.pdf), the Council has committed to planting 3,000 new trees on Council land by 2030 and to increasing canopy cover from c18% to c25%. Implementation of the Strategy received a boost in November 2021 when a grant of \u00a320,000 was secured from the Urban Tree Challenge Fund, match funded by Reading Borough Council, to plant additional trees over and above the Council's 2030 target.",
