        "sector": "Stationary energy: Energy efficiency/ retrofit measures addressing existing commercial, residential and/or municipal buildings",
        "description": "Schools energy efficiency and solar programme:\u2022In March 2021, the Council was awarded \u00a3556k for school solar panels and just over \u00a3800k for schools energy efficiency projects from the UK Government's Public Sector Decarbonisation Scheme.\u2022The funding, combined with the Council's own Education Capital Grant, has enabled 6 double glazing projects, 3 roof insulation projects, 6 LED lighting projects, and 20 solar PV projects across the school estate. \u2022All of these projects are now completed. These are the first steps to decarbonising the school buildings - reducing heat loss, electricity consumption and generating renewable electricity will pave the way to switch to a renewable heat source (heat pumps) in future\u2022Further funding bids for funding to progress 3 school renewable heat projects are planned in the Autumn.The programme represents a significant investment in the current and future energy performance of the schools estate, saving 91.54 tonnes of carbon per year or 5,671 tonnes over the lifetime of the products. School emissions have reduced by 39% since 2008 to 2023, a year on year reduction of 223.7 tonnes.",
