        "sector": "Generation of grid-supplied energy: Low or zero carbon energy supply generation",
        "description": "The Council invested heavily in energy efficiency and renewable energy in its new headquarters building (the Civic Centre) when it moved into the building in 2014-15. At the time the rooftop solar array was the largest on any local authority HQ in the country. \u00a31.3m of the \u00a325m refurbishment was earmarked for energy saving investment. The move to the new HQ enabled disposal of other buildings. The carbon savings quoted below are based on energy consumption from 2017/18 (the first year of occupation of the new Civic Centre) compared with that for 2014/15 (the last year of occupation of the old Civic Centre) and include the carbon savings from associated disposals enabled by the move. The Council has now invested in a further phase of low carbon investment in the Civic Centre, with a \u00a32.4 million heat pump project at the Civic Centre which which was completed in 2025 Please note the estimated annual emissions savings for this action are also included in the larger figure (16,797) quoted for the 'Action to advance net zero carbon in municipal buildings' action listed above. Further savings are expected from a \u00a37m project to incorporate the towns main library into the civic offices and allow the repurposing of the old library building which is likely to be converted into housing but will become a rebuild/refurbishment project so reducing emissions considerably.",
