        "sector": "Stationary energy: On-site renewable energy generation",
        "description": "A Large rooftop solar array has been designed and is currently awaiting legal approval on Readings bus depot roof. The panels will help to supply electricity to the fleet of electric buses which have recently been acquired. The array is a total of 300kWp, making it the largest single rooftop array in the town.",
        "status": "2025",
        "cobenefits": "2046",
        "financeStatus": "Estimated reduction in annual inventory emissions due to action",
        "totalCost": null,
