        "sector": "Transportation: Improve walking, cycling and integrated transit access",
        "description": "Mobility and transport makes up 871,376 tCO2e\\n(25%) of Powys' Carbon Footprint. A mix of quantitative data on emissions hotspots and qualitative assessments, including their feasibility and wider policy alignment has identified this area as a priority intervention area. \\n\\nThis action includes investing in infrastructure which promotes walking and cycling and public transport usage to reduce short car trips, leading to lower emissions.",
