        "impacts": "Sandwell is a heavily urbanised borough with unequal distribution of sustainable drainage systems. The river Tame flows through the borough, as well as a number of underground diverted streams and an extensive canal network that runs through high population areas. While flooding events related to these rivers and canals are infrequent, a combination of poor natural drainage, heavy urbanisation and lack of preparedness mean many areas are at risk of flood events in a changing climate.",
