        "impacts": "Heat stress will disproportionately impact on our poorest residents, marginalised groups, and those most medically vulnerable. Sandwell has a high proportion of deprived and marginalised communities, and resources and messaging will be difficult to distribute to these communities in times of need. As recent times have shown, the borough is not equipped to deal with prolonged heat, and the poorest residents often live in ill equipped and poorly insulated homes that are impacted most. Furthermore, as an industrial-heavy borough, Sandwell has many residents that would feel the biggest impacts in their workplaces, with high heat industries and the construction sector being most widely affected.",
