        "sectorsExposed": "Forestry|Conservation|Human health and social work activities",
        "impacts": "Green space is extremely valuable to residents' health, wellbeing, nature connectedness, and protection from climate hazards. However, as a heavily urbanised area with a shortage of good quality housing, green space is always under threat. Sandwell also does not have a good even spread of accessible green space in the borough, with some areas having much better access than others - often in wealthier communities. With increasing pressure on green spaces, and the effects of a changing climate, there is a risk of this provision being reduced, through land use changes and loss of growing space - residents are at risk of losing valuable green infrastructure and the benefits it provides.",
