        "sectorsExposed": "Sewerage, waste management and remediation activities|Arts, entertainment and recreation|Conservation|Fishing|Water supply|Agriculture|Forestry|Human health and social work activities|Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply",
        "impacts": "Increase in heat stress and related illnesses and health impacts for vulnerable groups and communities.\\n\\nIncreased pressure on the public water supply and impacts upon community resilience.\\n\\nIncrease in the incidence and severity of drought conditions could lead to water shortages.\\n\\nBuildings & infrastructure may be at an increased fire risk due to seasonal changes in climatic conditions.\\n\\nOver-abstraction can cause low flows in the summer months which can result in pressures on water supply, water quality and the ecology of rivers. \\n\\nLow flow rates will have a harmful impact on water quality and the ecological status of rivers and their associated wetlands.\\n\\nRivers and water bodies are likely to be more sensitive to diffuse pollution from agricultural activity, saline intrusion in coastal areas, urban and road related run-off and sewage leakage.\\n\\nReduced precipitation and increased intensity and duration of drought may effect supply of water for agricultural use.\\n\\nHigher summer temperatures and Increased period of drought will impact on agriculture, crop production and livestock farming.\\n\\n Reduced availability of water supply for livestock causing dehydration, heat stress and other animal welfare issues.\\n\\nInsufficient water supply to support grazing of remote or high drought prone areas - reductions in stocking rates due to drought pressure and impacts upon agri-business viability.\\n\\nReduced flows to surface waters due to drought and over-abstraction. Greater incidences of algal blooms and concentration of pollutants in rivers and stream due to reduced flows.\\n\\nHigher exterior temperatures and increased low-level ozone formation resulting in poor air-quality.\\n\\nExacerbation of non-communicable disease and health conditions - such as cardiovascular and respiratory disease.\\n\\nExposure to poor air quality, increasing of respiratory illnesses and risk of premature death or vulnerable groups.\\n\\nExtreme heat and exposure to excessive heat and sun may impact vulnerable groups or people working outside.\\n\\nOverwhelming of local health services provision due to increased demand.\\n\\n",
