        "impacts": "Built Environment\\n\\nGreater risk of flooding due to increased occurrence and severity of weather events.\\n\\nIncreased incidence and severity of flooding could overwhelm or damage existing drainage and flood defence and infrastructure.\\n\\nRisk of flooding of commercial and businesses properties within river valleys and low-lying areas.\\n\\nCommunities and residential properties near to or adjoining river corridors or within flood plain areas are at an increased risk of flooding.\\n\\nRisk of loss of life, injury and longer-term impacts upon well-being and social cohesion for communities that are affected by flooding.\\n\\nLoss of livelihood, personal belongings and increased cost of insurance. High risk areas and properties may become uninsurable as the risks, severity and frequency of flooding incidents increases over time.\\n\\nBusiness and economic activity in rural areas are impacted. Direct economic impact on rural businesses of flooding and damage to property. Loss of livelihood and Increased cost of insurance.\\n\\nImpact on essential local services for some smaller and more remote communities - particularly for emergency services, hospital treatment and healthcare.\\n\\nRoads and other rural access corridors become difficult to use or impassable due to poor ground conditions or flooding.\\n\\nBridges and other infrastructure may be damaged by debris or washed away by river flooding. Access to some remote communities may become more restricted for longer periods of time.\\n\\nFarming and land-based sector\\n\\nIncreased incidence and severity of flooding could overwhelm or damage existing water and drainage infrastructure.\\n\\nRisk of flooding of properties and agricultural land within river valleys and low-lying areas \\n\\nInundation and flooding or farm land adjoining rivers or within flood plains - loss of crops, damage to farm assets and equipment, risk of loss and welfare impacts upon livestock.\\n\\n\\n\\nEcological and cultural heritage assets\\n\\nIncreased risk of loss of ecological, heritage or archaeological sites from flooding or inundation.\\n\\nImpact upon the integrity of buried archaeology particularly where there may be waterlogged features that are best preserved in situ.\\n\\nDamage and deterioration of scheduled monuments or features caused by flooding or waterlogging.\\n\\nLoss of archaeological sites or assets in coastal areas as a result of storm damage, flooding, land- slides or cliff falls\\n\\n",
