        "sector": "Stationary energy: Building codes and standards",
        "description": "Sustainable construction (Supplementary Planning Document)\\n\\n The SDNPA have adopted a sustainable construction SPD. This provides further guidance on the implementation of Local Plan policies - specifically Policy SD2 - Ecosystem Services, SD22 - Where it relates to EV Charging points and SD48 Climate Change and sustainable use of resources.\\n\\nThe SPD also covers a number of detailed matter including energy and water efficiency, use of low or zero carbon energy, sustainable materials, minimising waste and adapting to climate change.\\n\\nThe SPD supports the Local Plan : Objective 6 - To adapt to and mitigate against the impacts of climate change. \\n\\nhttps://www.southdowns.gov.uk/planning-policy/supplementary-planning-documents/supplementary-planning-documents/sustainable-construction-supplementary-planning-document/\\n\\nHaving been adopted it is now a material consideration for any planning application within the National Park.\\n\\nThe South Downs is one of the largest and busiest planning authorities in the UK. With around 7,500 applications per year. So this has potential to aggregate up in terms of the sustainable build and other factors relevant to mitigation.",
