        "description": "Since late 2022 Sunderland City Council has installed approximately 1.6 MW(p) of solar PV at 11 sites, including schools such as Hetton Primary and Barnes Junior's Dining Block. This investment also includes in excess of 3MWh of associated battery storage. These solar panels will generate approximately 1440 MWh per annum and save an anticipated 324 tonnes of carbon and reduce cost by \u00a3400,000 per annum. \\n\\nAdditional funding has been agreed by Sunderland City Council (August 2024) to enable additional solar PV to be installed at operational buildings and schools during 2025/26 and 2026/27. A new Solar PV procurement framework is to be approved by Cabinet in September 2025 to enable the implementation of all works across Sunderland schools and other Council operational sites.",
