        "focusAreas": "Emissions reduction|Transport (Mobility)",
        "description": "The Council continues to work closely with Better Points, an app that tracks travel movements via GPS using smartphones and rewards participants with points for using more sustainable modes of transport like walking, cycling and using public transport as a pilot project. Extended until December 2025, currently (July 2025) there are 4,011 registered users and engagement rates have been very high throughout the project. In 23/24 a total of 307,392 sustainable trips were recorded covering 488,195 miles. After 10,785 trips we asked 'did this replace a solo car journey?' and 6,407 responses (59%) were 'yes'. Extrapolated, this suggests 290,000 car trips and 61.6 tonnes of CO2 emissions were avoided. The value of the latter, according to DESNZ, is \u00a315,770 and the top 3 modes are walking (75%), cycling (9%) and bus (12%). Sunderland University and Sunderland College have partnered with BetterPoints and offer free drinks in their campus cafes when redeeming points, with competitions and bonus prizes to encourage students to travel actively. Active Sunderland and other big events taking place across the City are promoted with push notifications whereby users are rewarded with extra points for travelling to them sustainably for example The Big Walk, The Big Bike Ride and on match days to the Stadium of Light.",
