        "impacts": "Extreme heat has a significant impact on the health of the population. Children, the elderly and those with medical conditions suffer more from the ill effects of heat e.g. heatstroke. Outdoor workers and construction workers are more exposed to the heat, so they are also more likely to suffer from its effects. Those with a low income are more likely to become ill from the heat, as they are less likely to be able to afford mitigating items like a fan, air conditioning. Water supplies and sewerage also suffer in the heat, as water can run out if drought hits, which makes it harder for residents to get water and for the sewage systems to work.",
