      "equitableDistribution": "Yes, the jurisdiction is engaging with frontline communities most impacted by climate change",
      "quantifiesEquity": "Unknown",
      "equityEvidence": "We have run the 'Community Accelerator' programme, where a contracted staff member worked with four rural communities a year to specifically support them with rural climate issues e.g. drainage at Great Alne, which frequently floods. We are planning to work with rural communities in Warwick District through the continued work of the Local Community Engagement programme to give them specific support on areas that will affect them more than urban dwellers e.g. flooding, putting in public transport links. We are running an event on he 17th of October where local community groups and town and parish councils will meet to learn more about how they can undertake climate projects in their areas and make connections with each other."
