        "sectors": "Other: The plan details that 'a robust monitoring and evaluation process needs to be developed alongside this Plan'. This is to be developed and will follow shortly.",
        "renewableTarget": "The plan uses data from the UKCP18 probabilistic projections and refers to two emission scenarios: RCP2.6 6 (roughly equivalent to a global warming +2\u00b0C above preindustrial scenario by 2100) and RCP6.0 (roughly equivalent to a global warming +4\u00b0C above preindustrial levels by 2100), with the exception of Sea Level Rise, where the RCP8.5 scenario is used, as for marine projections this is closer to a +4\u00b0C global warming scenario (it is worth noting that the plan highlights how Sea Level Rise is not a significant risk to the West Midlands, besides from movement of people, impact on supply chains and transport infrastructure). The plan utilises methodology and findings from the Independent Assessment for UK Climate Risk (CCRA3).",
