        "sectors": "Other: The WMCA Adaptation Project Officer will update the Adaptation Plan annually, identifying and evaluating progress through workshop sessions with colleagues across directorates. However this evaluation will not be published.|Evaluation: Evaluation of plan takes place annually or more frequently than annually|Monitoring: Information on progress of plan is monitored and publicly reported annually or more frequently than annually",
        "renewableTarget": "The WMCA is using climate impacts from UKCP 18 (from the Met Office) to identify the risks to be considered. This data informed the WMCA's Climate Impacts Report (2022: https://www.wmca.org.uk/documents/environment-energy/a-summary-of-climate-change-impacts-in-the-west-midlands-combined-authority-area/a-summary-of-climate-change-impacts-in-the-west-midlands-combined-authority-area/climate-projections/) which has provided a high-level account of climate-related scenarios to inform the Adaptation Action Plan.",
