        "comment": "The WMCA has been in conversation with Defra around devolution adaptation asks to seek to formalise regional and local authorities responsibilities in national adaptation governance. In 2025 the WMCA launched its first Integrated Settlement and in 2026, there are plans to introduce an Environment and Climate pillar to this settlement. The WMCA are in ongoing negotiations with Defra on the potential to pilot a regional approach to climate risk management and adaptation planning. This is dependent on the availability of national resources to support any potentially devolved responsibilities for adaptation. Through the WMCA's statutory role as Local Nature Recovery Strategy (LNRS) responsible authority, it is ensuring that adaptation is both an outcome of nature recovery and that nature recovery itself is adapted to future climate scenarios."
