        "comment": "WM2041 is a region wide Net Zero target that all of the seven consistent Local Authorities in the West Midlands have agreed to, through the necessary political processes. As a result, all of the local authorities are working towards 2041 as the latest date, however a couple of Local Authorities, such as Birmingham City Council, are aiming for net zero by 2030."
