        "focusAreas": "Public health|Adaptation|Resilience|Natural environment",
        "description": "The WMCA lead the West Midlands-Adapt project in partnership with the University of Birmingham. The \u00a32m, UKRI-funded project seeks to drive a step change in regional climate adaptation through three workstreams: (1) community engagement and ward-scale climate adaptation planning, (2) improvements to the region's Climate Risk & Vulnerability Assessment (CRVA) methodology and (3) building regional adaptive capacity through the establishment of a Regional Adaptation Network (RAN). The RAN is convened by the WMCA and meets quarterly. It currently has over 140 registered members. Through neighbourhood focused climate adaptation, WM-Adapt is seeking to support the most vulnerable communities in each local authority to develop resilience to climate impacts. ",
