        "comment": "The Climate Risk and Vulnerability Assessment identifies the likelihood of future climate hazards and their potential impacts across Westminster, including on lives, livelihoods, health and wellbeing, ecosystems and species, economic, social, and cultural assets, services, industries, and infrastructure. The CRVA is framed around the climate risks identified in the national Climate Change Risk Assessment published by the UK Government in 2022"
