        "description": "We recognise that collaboration with our local residents, businesses and other stakeholders is key in delivering our action plan and meeting our 2030 target. Therefore, there are a number of mechanisms utilised in order to deliver this, including significantly: - Publicly reporting on the climate action plan progress annually to full council. - Consulting with stakeholders on major new projects and strategies. - Engaging with stakeholders as part of a community deliberative process to both provide more knowledge and gain more insight into their understanding around the action plan and potential additions or improvements. These group events covered the majority of key areas being targeted by the action plan focusing on waste & recycling, homes & energy, how we travel and behaviour change. - Engagement is also increased through newsletters and social media campaigns, including a climate emergency hub for detailed information and links to other resources.",
