        "focusAreas": "Energy|Natural environment|Emissions reduction|Building and Infrastructure",
        "description": "We are continually engaging with other local authorities who have delivered successful work or research, often following webinars, in order to share knowledge and incorporate these ideas into our own action plans and policies where possible. This includes a specific meeting to share best practice with equivalent climate officers of other councils. Meanwhile, we are also working with other nearby authorities on a number of larger projects which cross council borders and benefit from shared expertise and scale, such as a energy reduction measures with Reading Council and collaboration around more efficient energy and transport infrastructure. We are also key members of a local authority advisory panel regarding adaptation, where best practice is shared and potential collaborative opportunities are discussed, including responding to national government consultations.",
