        "govtLevelsEngaged": "Lower level of government|National-level government",
        "engagementPurpose": "The development of this component is required by the national government (e.g., by law, regulation and/or agreement)",
        "comment": "Under the Protected Landscapes Targets and Outcomes Framework (PLTOF) each Protected Landscape (including this Authority) has adopted their share of the following climate mitigation targets:\\n\\nTarget 6:Reduce net greenhouse gas emissions in Protected Landscapes to net zero by 2050 relative to 1990 levels.\\nTarget 7: Peat: Restore approximately 130,000 hectares of peat in Protected Landscapes by 2050. \\nTarget 8: Increased tree canopy and woodland cover: Increase tree canopy and woodland cover (combined) by 3% of total land area in Protected Landscapes by 2050 (from 2022 baseline).\\n\\nThe Authority, alongside the other Protected Landscapes, will report on performance against National Targets 1-10, which relate which relate to carbon reduction, wildlife, sustainable farming, accessibility and nature recovery. The first report is due in 2025.\\n\\nThe Authority is in the process of engaging further with the UK Government regarding further refinement and optimisation of PLTOF, through a joint group of National Park officers and invited government representatives."
